<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/ThePatriot/int_192fb48d'>Film: The Patriot / int_192fb48d</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>The British in general get this, but Big Bad Charles Cornwallis definitely does. While in the movie he is still portrayed as a Noble Demon in comparison to Tavington's plain demon, he still holds the colonists in open contempt and disdain. In reality Cornwallis was a Whig who was sympathetic to the colonials, and before the war was an MP who voted on their behalf several times.</i></td>
</tr>


