<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a name='int_6e4d8ebc' href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/ThePatriot/int_6e4d8ebc'>Film: The Patriot / int_6e4d8ebc</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type'>type</div></td>
<td><a href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Main/HeelFaceDoorSlam'>Heel Face Door Slam</a></td>
</tr>


<tr class="bg1"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/ThePatriot/int_6e4d8ebc'>Film: The Patriot / int_6e4d8ebc</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>Heel Face Door Slam: The British lieutenant who thanked Martin for helping British soldiers after the first battle is shown to look horrified at the shooting of Thomas and the massacre of the enemy wounded. And then the movie has him die first when Martin and his sons rescue Gabriel. Then there's Wilkins, who protests the burning of the church and looks visibly upset by it, but nothing is ever done with it and he is forgotten about during the final battle, with no real resolution to his character.</i></td>
</tr>


<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/ThePatriot/int_6e4d8ebc'>Film: The Patriot / int_6e4d8ebc</a></td>
