<tr class="bg0"><td>&nbsp;</td><td><a  href='http://dbtropes.org/resource/Film/ThePatriot/int_ca4e088f'>Film: The Patriot / int_ca4e088f</a></td>
<td><div title='http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment'>comment</div></td>
<td><i>Everyone Has Standards: Cornwallis is an honorable British general who respects the laws of warfare and simply wants to re-establish British rule. He also wants to maintain good, if not peaceful, relations with the colonials. However, he is still appalled at Tavington's brutal tactics and rightly faults him for the increasing resistance against the British from the American militia. Also, one of Tavington's men complains that there's no honor in burning down a church full of civilians, and is clearly reluctant to follow his orders to do so.</i></td>
</tr>


